Package: crab-certbundle
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, python3, openssl
Description: OpenSSL-style CA certificate directory builder for research infrastructure
 CRAB (Certificate Root Anchor Builder) generates and updates hashed CApath
 directories suitable for XRootD, dCache, curl/OpenSSL consumers, and similar
 data-movement middleware used in research computing (SRCNet, WLCG, EGI).
 .
 Features: atomic directory replacement, policy engine (CA flag, expiry, EKU,
 IGTF policy-tag filtering), CRL fetch and freshness validation, diff mode,
 dry-run mode, JSON output, and a built-in test CA (crabctl ca / cert).
 .
 Python 3.6.8+ compatible; no dependency on OSG, VOMS, or grid middleware.
 All Python runtime dependencies are vendored under
 /usr/share/crab-certbundle/vendor so the package does not conflict with
 system Python packages.
